CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 21, 1963, pg. 3 reads: "Mourning the death of Willis Curley of 215 Burrows St., Pittsburgh, are Mrs. Curley, the widow, and the six children of the Curleys. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of surviving family members of car accident victim Willis Curley, including his wife Mrs. Curley seated center, surrounded by two sons and four daughters, on bench in front of building in Terrace Village
